As it is, this change will break the API backwards compatibility.

Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)

Patch Set 3:

I tested out this patch.  When an image signature verification fails, the image is in status 'killed' and the data has been removed from the backend.  The image location status, however, remains 'active' until the image record is deleted.

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Not sure what i mentioned in the previous comment is bad, just wanted to point it out.  I think our image-lifecycle functional tests show that this change is not causing any regressions.  Not +2ing because I think Erno may have a few more questions.

Patch Set 3: Code-Review-2

(1 comment)

I just want to be very clear that this approach will some day come and bite us. As when I was reviewing this, it's not obvious what is happening here. I flagged the place in the location.py L447 where we need to put the logic for cleanout.
